More condolences and eulogies have continued to pour in for the late Juju maestro, Dayo Kujore, who died on Monday, January 10, 2022. Evergreen music’s topshot, Bimbo Esho, in a statement, eulogised the late singer. Esho recounted her last days with the late Kujore. She said: “I remembered I chatted with the great icon a few weeks ago discussing about an event our company Evergreen Music and National Theatre was putting together in December. “I remember with nostalgia the day I sent him his picture taken from an album sleeve from our archive. - Advertisement -   Having s3x on first date doesn’t make you cheap – Blessing…     Social media reacts as Davido reveals 2022 motto     Wife celebrates Seun Kuti at 39   “He told me he was just 18 years old in the picture and he reminisced how he received tutelage under Prince Adekunle before forming his band.” Esho also revealed that she found out that Kujore died after a brief illness. “I was at a meeting somewhere in Surulere when a friend called me to ask me if I heard the news of Wonder Dayo Kujore’s death. I was in great shock. “Immediately I put a call through to his number to authenticate the news. The woman who picked his phone didn’t allow me to talk and she said straight away ‘Aunty Bimbo what you want to confirm is true.’ “The woman introduced herself as his wife and said he had been ill.” The music executive further explained that the demise of Kujore is touching because he was just returning to the limelight with his last album ‘Wisdom.’